article.headline: Toledo 72, Bowling Green 64
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Florentino Valencia and Justin Ingram each had 15 points and Toledo scored its final 10 points on foul shots to beat Bowling Green 72-64 on Saturday night. The Rockets (13-9, 6-8 Mid-American Conference) hit their last field goal when Kashif Payne scored on a layup with 2:06 left for a 62-57 lead. Valencia, who was 7-of-10 at the line, hit two free throws with 1:46 left and John Amos made three, Keonta Howell and Ingram each hit two and Payne added one in the final minute to maintain the lead. Payne had 14 points and Howell 13 for the Rockets, who were 24-of-36 at the line including 10-of-12 down the stretch. Martin Samarco and John Floyd each scored 17 points and Matt Lefeld each had 11 for the Falcons (9-14, 5-8). It was the 154th meeting between the rivals. Toledo now holds an 80-74 advantage.
